title: Zarco wins Malaysian GP Moto2 race
text:
Zarco wins Malaysian GP Moto2 race Published: 25 October 2015 3:18 PM 
World Champion Johann Zarco won the Moto2 race of the 2015 Malaysian Motorcycle Grand Prix at the Sepang Circuit today. The Frenchman clocked 40:37.772s. – Reuters pic, October 25, 2015. Ajo Motorsports rider and 2015 Moto2 class World Champion Johann Zarco won the Moto2 class race of the 2015 Malaysian Motorcycle Grand Prix at the Sepang Circuit today. 
The Frenchman clocked 40 minutes and 37.772 seconds. 
Switzerland's Thomas Luthi of Derendinger Racing Interwetten finished in second place with 40:38.370s while Germany's Jonas Folger of AGR Team was in third place with 40:47.618s. 
Malaysian rider, Hafizh Syahrin Abdullah completed his race in eighth place clocking 41:04.457s, while Azlan Shah Kamaruzaman (Idemitsu Honda Team Asia) and Ramdan Rosli (Petronas AHM Malaysia) finished in 16th and 24th position, respectively, in 41:19.384s and 41:56.306s. – Bernama, October 25, 2015.
